# High-Performance Hybrid Observability Engine (LGTM Architecture)

This repository holds the architecture and configuration orchestration to instantiate a unified, highly integrated observability pipeline on an EC2 instance. The infrastructure mixes native OS system daemons for bare-metal metrics gathering with an agile, containerized Docker Compose loop for distributed logging and tracing topologies.

---

## Observability Architecture Map

The interaction mesh highlights how components isolated inside Docker interact seamlessly with system infrastructure and data planes via precise port boundaries.

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph Host_Machine ["EC2 Linux Host Environment"]
        Prometheus["Prometheus Daemon (:9090)"]
        NodeExporter["Node Exporter Daemon (:9100)"]
        Grafana["Grafana Server Dashboard (:3000)"]
    end

    subgraph Container_Fabric ["Docker Compose Bridge Network"]
        direction TB
        ChaosApp["chaos-app <br> (FastAPI / Uvicorn)"]
        WeatherApp["weather-service <br> (Backend)"]
        Alloy["Grafana Alloy Container (:4317/:4318)"]
        Loki["Grafana Loki Engine (:3100)"]
        Tempo["Grafana Tempo Engine (:3200)"]
    end

    %% Infrastructure Metrics Collection
    NodeExporter -->|Exposes Host OS Metrics| Prometheus
    Prometheus -->|Scrapes Self & Exporter| Prometheus

    %% Application Logs Loop
    ChaosApp -.->|Emits JSON stdout| DockerSocket[("/var/run/docker.sock")]
    WeatherApp -.->|Emits JSON stdout| DockerSocket
    DockerSocket --->|Scraped via Socket Mount| Alloy
    Alloy --->|Pushes Structured LogQL Streams| Loki

    %% OpenTelemetry Traces Loop
    ChaosApp ===>|Auto-Instrumented OTLP gRPC| Alloy
    WeatherApp ===>|Auto-Instrumented OTLP gRPC| Alloy
    Alloy ===>|Forwards OTLP Batches :4327| Tempo

    %% Consumption Layer Connections
    Grafana -->|Queries Prometheus TSDB| Prometheus
    Grafana -->|Queries Log Streams via HTTP| Loki
    Grafana -->|Queries Traces via HTTP| Tempo
    Tempo -.->|Trace-To-Logs Correlation Link| Loki